# dep-age-gate allowlist — the escape hatch for an urgent dependency bump that
# must land BEFORE its release-age window elapses (see tools/cmd/depgate).
#
# emisar is a security product, so the normal rule is: a freshly-published
# dependency release waits out its cooldown window before it can merge. The one
# legitimate exception is an urgent security fix — a patch for an actively
# exploited CVE in a dependency — where waiting is the larger risk. That is a
# deliberate, reviewable decision, so it leaves a paper trail here rather than a
# silent flag or a CI override.
#
# One entry per line:  <ecosystem> <package> <version> <reason>
#   ecosystem  hex | go | npm
#   package    exact package/module name as it appears in the lockfile
#   version    exact version being allowed (hex/npm: "1.2.3", go: "v1.2.3")
#   reason     REQUIRED, non-empty — the CVE / advisory id and why it can't wait
#
# The reason is mandatory: a bare exemption is a hard error. Remove the entry
# once the version has aged past its window (the gate would pass on its own then).
#
# Example (delete once real entries exist):
#   hex plug 1.99.1 GHSA-xxxx-yyyy-zzzz — RCE in Plug.Conn, patched only in 1.99.1, actively exploited
